I've created the Layouts guide document at `docs/generated/layouts.md`. The document covers all four layout types in dali-ui:

- **AbsoluteLayout**: Explicit pixel positioning with proportional sizing options via `AbsoluteLayoutFlags`
- **StackLayout**: Simple vertical or horizontal stacking with weight-based space distribution
- **FlexLayout**: CSS Flexbox-style layout with direction, wrap, grow/shrink, and alignment controls
- **GridLayout**: Row and column-based grid with absolute, star, and auto sizing

All code examples are adapted from the sample files in `repos/dali-ui/samples/` and verified against the public API headers in `repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/public-api/layouts/`. The document uses only allowed symbols from the dali-ui public API surface and follows the View-based object model.
